Class DataCluster

  • java.lang.Object

  • Direct Known Subclasses:

    public class DataCluster
extends Object

      • crop

        public DataCluster crop(String root)
        Crop the current data cluster with a copied cluster with the cropped information. For example if you have

        foo:
        . bar:
        . . foobar: 5
        . . foobar2:
        . . . foo:
        . . . . bard: 5

        and invoke DataCluster.crop("foo.bar"); it will return

        foobar: 5
        foobar2:
        . foo:
        . . bard: 5
        Parameters:
        root -
        Returns:
